summary: A 50-year-old man on a ketogenic diet who performs sprinting and reports 9 hours of sleep presents with headache and nausea in the setting of increased stress. His vital signs are unremarkable with a normal temperature, and no other lab or imaging data are currently available.
options: Hypoglycemia (relative to ketogenic diet and exercise)
Electrolyte imbalance (e.g., sodium or magnesium deficiency)
